<HL>
   Advanta Authorizes Buy-Back
</HL>
<DATE>
08/08/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ADVN
</CO>
<IN>
BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)
DIVIDENDS (DIV)
</IN>
<LP>
   HORSHAM, Pa. -- Advanta Corp. said its board authorized
the purchase of 200,000 of its common shares, bringing its
total 1990 stock buy-back authorization to 600,000 shares.
   Advanta also increased its quarterly dividend to three
cents a share from 2.5 cents, payable Sept. 18 to stock of
record Aug. 31.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The financial services holding company said stock
purchases may be made in the open market or through
negotiated transactions. The board recently completed the
buy-back of 400,000 shares, an action it approved in
February. As of June 30, the company had 9,426,000 shares
outstanding.
</TEXT>
